history.content: I would say it's fine to take it concurrently but not before 61C. I am in 164 right now, and up until a mid-Marchish, no 61C knowledge was really required. I think by the time 164 reaches related topics, 61C will have already taught the material you will need. I do not think that the EECS department enforces prereqs.

I'm strongly considering taking CS 164 next semester, but I will be taking 61C at the same time. I know it's a prerequisite, but is it really necessary to take 61C in order to take 164? 

What do you guys think / has anyone been in a similar situation? For that matter, are prerequisites even enforced during enrollment?
history.subject: Skip CS 164 prerequisites?
